The victims, aged 27 and 54, were held hostage in their Begonia Street home. The 41-year-old officer was stationed at the Lentegeur police station and it is believed the murders and suicide were a result of an argument that occurred between the couple on Wednesday. Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said: “Circumstances surrounding a hostage situation this morning at 9.10am in Begonia Street, Lentegeur, are being investigated. "According to information at hand, it was a 41-year-old police member who worked at Lentegeur (station).” Inquest cases were under investigation, Rwexana said. Shots were heard coming from the residence just after 9am yesterday morning. Police left the scene just after 1pm yesterday.